data.text:
To ensure meetingselect.com is functioning properly, Meetingselect uses cookies.

What are cookies?

Cookies collect information necessary for the correct functioning of a website. Meetingselect cookies are safe. They can not collect any personal information and are safe for your PC, laptop, phone or tablet.

How long do cookies stay?

Most cookies of meetingselect disappear when you close your browser. You can remove yourself at any time through your browser.

What do we do with cookies?

We use cookies for saving your preferences. If a visitor uses the Meetingselect platform via a partner, tracking data can be shared with that partner.

What cookies do we use?

Necessarry cookies These cookies are necessary for the platform to function. They are usually only set in response to actions made by you which amount to a request for services, such as setting your privacy preferences, logging in, or filling in forms.

Analytical cookies These cookies help us to understand how visitors engage with the platform. We may use a set of cookies to collect information and report site usage statistics.

Advertisement cookies Some common applications of cookies are to select advertising based on what’s relevant to a user; to improve reporting on ad campaign performance; and to avoid showing ads the user has already seen.
